# Shell scripts must always check out with LF line endings — they run
# under bash (WSL / Linux), where stray CR bytes break heredoc
# terminators and `#!` shebang lines.  Without this, core.autocrlf on a
# Windows checkout would rewrite them to CRLF and corrupt them (this is
# exactly what broke the GDRE Tools installer — see installer/install_gdre.sh).
*.sh text eol=lf
